<section id="section-1" class="p_section p_section--text text" style="padding-top: 70px;  padding-bottom: 70px;">

  <div class="ufo--p-container-fluid">
    <div class="text-container">
      <div class="text">
        <h3>Problem</h3>
        <p>When conducting transactions at a Bitcoin ATM, users must have a cryptocurrency wallet to receive their
          purchase. Companies like <a rel="nofollow" href="https://bitstop.co/" target="_blank">Bitstop</a> allow users to scan their
          wallets, insert cash into the ATM, and receive Bitcoin straight to their wallet.</p>
        <p>BREAD (BRD) Wallet offered iOS users a Bitcoin centric option for conducting such transactions, making the
          process simple and secure even for first-time users. However, following BRD’s ICO and the wallet’s
          incorporation of alternative cryptocurrencies, changes to the UI/UX caused significant confusion amongst
          users. This situation generated a significant increase in Bitstop customer service tickets from confused iOS
          users who were left open to potential losses from fraudulent transactions.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</section>
